    <p>
      <strong>Summary</strong>
    </p>
    <div xmlns="">
      <p>
        Originally appearing in the
        <em>Dangerous Women</em>
        anthology and now available as a
      solo ebook,
        <em>Shadows for Silence in the Forests of Hell</em>
        is a
      chilling novella of the Cosmere, the universe shared by
      Brandon Sanderson's Mistborn series and the #1
        <em>New York Times</em>
        bestselling Stormlight Archive.
      </p>
      <p>When the familiar and seemingly safe turns lethal, therein
      danger lies. Amid a forest where the shades of the dead
      linger all around, every homesteader knows to follow the
      Simple Rules: "Don't kindle flame, don't shed the blood of
      another, don't run at night. These things draw shades."
      Silence Montane has broken all three rules on more than one
      occasion. And to protect her family from a murderous gang
      with high bounties on their heads, Silence will break every
      rule again, at the risk of becoming a shade herself.</p>
    </div>
